  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-03 sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This synthetic adversarial sample embeds a future-dated validation evidence record whose evidenceTimestamp falls after the package signatureTimestamp, representing a subtle race-condition artifact (W-CON-03).",
