    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps at MRL 5, the assessment team determined that the combined evidence — GCI below 1.2% for primary velocity gradient QoIs, MAE of 8.3% against experimental NIH measurements, and Monte Carlo UQ on primary boundary conditions — provides sufficient credibility for the intended low-consequence exploratory use. Remaining epistemic gaps in model form, use error, and test sample representativeness are acknowledged and accepted under the Low assurance level designation. All supporting evidence records reviewed and incorporated.",
